Spin vectors carry frequently the super-index :math:`^z`, or :math:`^n`, or
:math:`^f`, to indicate unambiguously whether its components are
provided in either of the three reference frames
:math:`(x\,y\,z)`, :math:`(u\,v\,n)`, or :math:`(p_i\,t_i\,f_i)`.
An example is :math:`\boldsymbol{S}^z`, or :math:`\boldsymbol{S}^n`, or
:math:`\boldsymbol{S}^f`.
